quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  40,51,"Verily We, surely We provide help to Our Messengers and those who have Believed in the life of this world and (also) the Day the Witnesses will stand forth"
  40,52,The Day their excuse does not benefit the transgressors; and for them is curse and for them will be the evil of abode
  40,53,"And surely, indeed, We delivered to Musa Al-Hudah (‘The Guidance’) and We caused Bani Israiel to inherit Al-Kitab —"
  40,54,(as) a Guide and Reminder for the possessors of intellect and knowledge
  40,55,"So show patience. Surely, Allah’s promise is truth; and invoke forgiveness for your wrong-doing, and praise (Allah) with the Praise of your Nourisher-Sustainer by the Ashi (from late afternoon till sunset) and by the Ibkar (early dawn till sunrise). [This refers to the Asr and Fajr Prayers]"
  40,56,"Verily, those who dispute in Ayaatillahe without (any) authority that came to them: there is not in their chests except a desire for greatness; (although) they will not be those who attain it. So seek refuge with Allah. Certainly He, He is the All-Hearer, the All-Seer"
  40,57,"Surely, the creation of the heavens and the earth is greater than the creation of mankind, but the majority of mankind do not know"
  40,58,And do not become equal the blind and the strong in eye-sight. And those who have Believed and did righteous deeds — and (these do) not become equal to the one who indulges in evil. Very little it is what you remind (yourselves or remind others)
  40,59,"Verily, the Hour is surely approaching. (There is) no doubt therein, but the majority of mankind do not Believe"
  40,60,"And your Nourisher-Sustainer said: “Invoke Me, I will respond to you. Verily, those who show pride and arrogance against paying Me obedience — soon they will enter Hell as humiliated and disgraced ones"